        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Stop Sexual Harassment in K-12 Act</b></p> <p>This bill outlines the role and duties of Title IX coordinators in elementary and secondary schools, including by requiring local educational agencies to increase the number of full-time employees designated to serve as a Title IX coordinator per specified student population. The bill also creates a grant program to train teachers and staff on how to respond to signs of sexual harassment and assault of students and requires the Department of Education to develop a sexual violence climate survey.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
